	"Your attack surface is only as small as your weakest link.",
	"If you didn't request it, don't click it.",
	"Backups are your last line of defense. Test them.",
	"Complexity is the enemy of security.",
	"The cloud is just someone else's computer. Secure it like yours.",
	"Assume breach. Plan accordingly.",
	"Least privilege: give access to what's needed, nothing more.",
	"Security is a process, not a product.",
	"Patch faster than attackers can exploit.",
	"Your password manager is your best friend.",
	"Defense in depth: one layer is never enough.",
	"Social engineering bypasses every firewall.",
	"Log everything. You'll thank yourself later.",
	"Encrypt at rest, encrypt in transit.",
	"The human is always the weakest link. Train them.",
	"If a control needs a meeting to explain, it will fail during an incident.",
	"Complexity doesn't make systems safer, it makes failures harder to see.",
	"Every exception you approve today becomes tomorrow's attack path.",
	"Security that depends on perfect behavior is already broken.",
	"If patching is your only mitigation, you don't have a mitigation.",
	"Alerts without owners are just background noise.",
	"You don't secure systems, you secure the gaps between them.",
	"The first exploit is rarely the one that causes the damage.",
	"Controls that slow engineers will eventually be bypassed.",
	"Most breaches succeed quietly before they succeed loudly.",
	"Compliance proves paperwork, not resilience.",
	"If you can't explain why a rule exists, remove it.",
	"Attackers don't need zero-days when misconfigurations are everywhere.",
	"Detection beats prevention when prevention is brittle.",
	"A system no one understands cannot be secured.",
	"Privilege creep is just technical debt wearing a badge.",
	"Logging everything is useless if you can't answer one good question.",
	"The best security tools reduce decisions, not add dashboards.",
	"Hardening after deployment is already late.",
	"Most incidents start as 'low risk' findings.",
	"Security debt compounds faster than technical debt.",
	"If rollback isn't planned, failure isn't contained.",
	"You don't stop attacks, you limit blast radius.",
	"Every manual process is an eventual outage or breach.",
	"Defense fails first where ownership is unclear.",
	"A quiet network is often more dangerous than a noisy one.",
	"The fastest attacker is the one already inside.",
	"Security that can't scale will be disabled.",
	"Perfect visibility is impossible, useful visibility is not.",
	"Controls must survive human error to be worth deploying.",
	"Incident response begins long before the incident.",
	"Threat models age faster than infrastructure.",
	"Every alert is a question, not an answer.",
	"Tools don't create security, decisions do.",
	"If engineers hate it, attackers will love it.",
	"Defense without context is just guesswork.",
	"Attack paths are rarely complex, just overlooked.",
	"Security fails at integration points, not components.",
	"If detection comes after damage, it's just reporting.",
	"Assumed breach is not pessimism, it's realism.",
	"Over-restrictive controls create shadow systems.",
	"Most security failures are design failures, not exploit failures.",
	"Visibility without action is theater.",
